In MSTest v4, the `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>(object, out T)` overload was removed. The replacement is to use the return value instead:

```csharp
// MSTest v3
Assert.IsInstanceOfType<FastProcessor>(processor, out var typed);

// MSTest v4
var typed = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<FastProcessor>(processor);
```

The generic `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>(object)` now returns `T` directly, so you capture the result via assignment instead of an `out` parameter.

